quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,1,"Highly Exalted is the One Who took His servant on a journey by night from the Inviolable Mosque{1}to the Farthest Mosque{2}, whose precincts We<a class=""sup""><sup>a </sup></a>have blessed, in order to show him of Our signs; indeed, He is the All-Hearing, the All-Seeing.",footnotes:1:Al-masjid Al-Harāmin Makkah.|2:Al-masjid Al-Aqsain Jerusalem.
  17,2,"And We brought Moses the Scripture and made it guidance for the Children of Israel<span class=""h"">: “Take<sup foot_note=""80418"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>none for trustee other than Me,"
  17,3,"<i class=""s"">(O) </i>offspring of those We carried with Noah; indeed, he was a constantly thankful servant.”"
  17,4,"And We decreed for the Children of Israel in the Scripture: “You will most surely corrupt in the land twice, and you will most surely rise to a great height."
  17,5,"Then when the promise of the first of the two times came true, We sent against you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>servants of Ours possessing intense force, and they ransacked the homes, and it was a promise fulfilled.”"
  17,6,"Then We gave you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>back your turn against them and supplied you with wealth and offspring and made you more numerous."
  17,7,"If you excel in doing good, you excel in doing good to your own benefit; and if you do evil, you do so against yourselves. Then when the promise of the second time comes true, <span class=""h"">they<sup foot_note=""80419"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span><span class=""h"">will defile</span>your faces, and they will enter the Mosque as they entered it the first time, and they will utterly destroy all that falls into their power."
